## Documentation Standards

> [!CAUTION]
> **Sensitive Data Rules:**
> - **NEVER** include secret values, API key tokens, or webhook secrets
> - **NEVER** include external/internal IP addresses or full FQDNs
> - **NEVER** include connection strings
> - Installation key UUIDs and sensor SIDs are safe to document

> [!NOTE]
> **Formatting Standards:**
> - Use `--oid` and `--output yaml` in all CLI commands
> - Use the full OID UUID — never the org name
> - Use Mermaid diagrams for data flows
> - Use collapsible `<details>` for large tables
> - Link to official LC docs (verified URLs only)

---

## Review Cadence

| Frequency | Action |
|-----------|--------|
| Weekly | Run export script, check for drift |
| Monthly | Full review of all documentation against live state |
| On change | Update docs immediately when making org changes |
| Quarterly | Review architecture diagrams and data flow accuracy |
